               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra (Maryam); name of the protagonist; name of the scribe; name of the commissioner and his children; some initial lines in Text I (e.g., fol. 15rb); a few lines alternating with black lines on the incipit page of Text II; incipits of miracles; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>In Text II, miracles 3, 5, 9 and 12 are not numbered. The numeral for miracle 11 is not readable.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="117vb"/>Colophon: fols. 117vb-118ra. Fol. 117vb: ተፈጸመ፡ በዝየ፡ ገድለ፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ መን[fol. 118ra]ፈስ[፡] ቅዱስ፡ … ለጸሐፊሃ፡ ኢያሱ። ወለዘአጽሐፎ፡ ወልደ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡  አሜን፨<foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                        <note>The note mentions the scribe ʾIyasu and the commissioner of the Ms. Wäldä Giyorgis.</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
